{"id": 14378, "source": "pestle", "subject": "biology", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "6-3-defence-against-infectious-disease", "title": "19M.1.HL.TZ2.36", "topic_id": "6", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>The blood of two men was tested and the results are shown. Anti-D refers to the rhesus blood group. Clotting indicates that antigens associated with a particular factor or blood group are present in a blood sample.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"/></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[Source: © International Baccalaureate Organization 2019]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The man who tested positive for anti-D was then tested for ABO blood group. These results were obtained.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"/></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[Source: © International Baccalaureate Organization 2019]</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What ABO blood group does the man testing positive for anti-D have?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A. A</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">B. B</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">C. AB</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">D. O</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Many candidates failed to realize that a negative reaction meant the antigens for A and for B were not present in the blood of the man tested.</p>\n</div>"}